<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When calling Zend_Http_Client::request, some valid URLs end up causing a Zend_Uri_Exception when they result in redirects in which relative paths are used in the HTTP response headers. A code example that exposes this is shown below.</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
require 'Zend/Http/Client.php';

$http = new Zend_Http_Client(null, array('timeout' =&gt; 10));
$http-&gt;setUri('<a href="http://portasoft.org">http://portasoft.org</a>');

$response = $http-&gt;request('HEAD');

/*
Output:
Fatal error: Uncaught exception 'Zend_Uri_Exception' with message 'Path "\/news.
php" is not a valid HTTP path' in Zend\Uri\Http.php:457
Stack trace:
#0 Zend\Http\Client.php(775): Zend_Uri_Http-&gt;setPath('\/news.php')
#1 test.php(7): Zend_Http_Client-&gt;request('HEAD')
#2 {main} thrown in Zend\Uri\Http.php on line 457
*/
</code></pre>

<p>Firefox 2 and curl 7.15.4 process this URL as expected. Below is the result of manually accessing each URL in the redirection from <a href="http://portasoft.org">http://portasoft.org</a> to the end of the redirection at <a href="http://www.portasoft.org/e107/news.php">http://www.portasoft.org/e107/news.php</a>.</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
